Package: shapeshiftr
Title: Detecting Population Range Reconfiguration via Inter-individual Distances
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Nicola", "Love", , "nicolalove@zoology.ubc.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A collection of tools to analyze shifts in the spatial cohesion of a group or population using inter-individual distances. Functions cvpop, cvind, and cvratio only require an input of a vector, matrix or dataframe of cartesian coordinates (x and y in separate columns). The function iidist requires a sf dataframe, the output of which can be used in cvmetrics_sf.  
